data.title: Salem tames Lisbon
data.meta_description: SALEM — Salem defeated Lisbon 190-232 on Thursday at Salem Hills Golf Club.   Tanner James led the Quakers with a 43, followed by Keegan Sommers with a 48,
data.text:
SALEM — Salem defeated Lisbon 190-232 on Thursday at Salem Hills Golf Club.

Tanner James led the Quakers with a 43, followed by Keegan Sommers with a 48, Caden Arcuri with a 49 and Eli James and Traevon Washington each with a 50.

For Lisbon, Logan Sturgeon shot a 54, Devan Fox added a 55, Marshall Hall had a 57 and Brady Chamberlain finished with a 66. Salem improves to 3-1.

The Quakers will next face United Local today at Salem Hills.

Dukes edge Warriors

BELOIT — Marlington’s girls golf team beat West Branch 184-190 on Thursday at Westville Lake.

For the Warriors, Katie Santee had a 38, Bella Linger 48, Emma McLaughlin 51 and Hayden Mesler 53.

Rebels fall in league match

COLUMBIANA — Liberty topped Crestview 177-184 on Thursday at Beaver Creek Meadows Golf Course.

Evan Bates led Liberty with a 37.

For Crestview, Braydon Gilbert and Peyton Conkle both shot 41s, followed by Caleb Booth with a 46, and Elaina Louk with a 56.

Crestview’s next match is set for Monday against Southeast at Olde Dutch Mill Golf Course.

Southern scores two EOAC wins

GUILFORD LAKE — Southern Local edged Wellsville and Leetonia in a tri-match on Thursday at Twin Springs Golf Course.

Southern Local had a 206, as Wyatt Bach paced the Indians with a 46, followed by Trevor Groff with a 48, Austin Harshbarger with a 53 and Preston Pitts with a 59.

Wellsville finished second with a score of 222.

Landen Ramsay led the Tigers with a 44, followed by Johnnie Tice with a 53, Gage Vance with a 65 and Cooper Frank with a 62.

Leetonia placed third with a team score of 236. Jeremiah Faulk led the Bears with a 53, followed by Chase Bondi with a 50 and Christian Kelly with a 65.

Southern Local improves to 3-2 on the season.

Weekly records ace

CALCUTTA — Joyce Weekly aced Beaver Creek Meadows’ 90-yard, No. 2 with a wedge on Thursday. She was playing with Anita Perone, Linda Danley and Bobbi Lang.
